-- Audi CEO Says 2012 Will Be Tougher Than 2011, Reuters Reports
-- B y   R a g n h i l d   K j e t l a n d
-- 2011-12-25T11:54:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-25/audi-ceo-says-2012-will-be-tougher-than-2011-reuters-reports.html
Rupert Stadler, chief executive
officer of  Volkswagen AG (VOW) ’s luxury unit Audi AG, said the
automotive industry faces a tougher year in 2012,  Reuters 
reported, citing an interview.  Stadler, who expects the industry to continue to grow over
the next 10 years, said he doesn’t want to succeed Volkswagen
CEO Martin Winterkorn when the latter steps down at the end of
2016, Reuters reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ragnhild Kjetland in Frankfurt at 
